  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Djibouti DM Capacity Strengthening Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Title:&#xC2;&#xA0;Disaster management capacity strengthening&#xC2;&#xA0;


Start and end dates:&#xC2;&#xA0;01/12/2016 &#xE2;&#x20AC;&#x201C; 31/12/2019 (decision to extend to end of 2020)&#xC2;&#xA0;


Summary:&#xC2;&#xA0;Focus is on engaging communities in DRR; responding to disasters and strengthening work with refugee, migrant and host communities. BRC will continue working alongside the ICRC and IFRC to stabilise the governance and management of the NS.&#xC2;&#xA0;


The&#xC2;&#xA0;program&#xC2;&#xA0;has two output areas: 
1) increase DRCS&#xE2;&#x20AC;&#x2122;&#xC2;&#xA0;disaster management capacity&#xC2;&#xA0;and 
2) responds to the needs of people affected by disasters in Djibouti.&#xC2;&#xA0;
Location:&#xC2;&#xA0;Djibouti&#xC2;&#xA0;&#xC2;&#xA0;


Beneficiaries:&#xC2;&#xA0;NA&#xC2;&#xA0;


Donor:&#xC2;&#xA0;GF&#xC2;&#xA0;


PNSs/Partners:&#xC2;&#xA0;BRC, CRD


Budget:&#xC2;&#xA0;2016-2019 = &#xC2;&#xA3;300,000.&#xC2;&#xA0;&#xC2;&#xA3;75,000 annual budgeted for up to 2021 (GF)&#xC2;&#xA0;


Current situation (Jan 2020):&#xC2;&#xA0;Focus has shifted from DM activities to supporting CRD in establishing a sound governance structure. In Q4 of 2019 CRD successfully carried out their first AGM in a long time and have appointed an interim board whose focus is rebuidling the governance structures. In 2020 BRC will support this initiative by funding key staff positions and policy development work.</narrative>
  </description>
